ZCZC GE28
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
TUESDAY TO FRIDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 212300 UTC
TUESDAY EVENING A STNR LOW 993 LIES AT N 59 W 23 WITH
SLACK FLOW ACROSS MOST OF THE UK AND CULLERCOATS. THE
AZORES HIGH ALSO EXTENDS ACROSS WERN NITON AT THIS TIME.
THE PATTERN REMAINS SIMILAR DURING WEDNESDAY BUT WITH A
WEAK TROUGH DEVELOPING ACROSS NERN PARTS OF CULLERCOATS
DURING THE MORNING BEFORE MOV INTO THE NORWEGIAN SEA
DURING THE AFTERNOON. AT THE SAME TIME THE AZORES HIGH
BUILDS FURTHER NE ACROSS THE UK AND THE LOW REMAINS STNR
IN THE ATLANTIC. REMAINING SIMILAR DURING THURSDAY WITH
THE LOW SINKING SWARDS AND FLN 1000 AND GENERALLY SLACK
FLOW CONTINUING ACROSS MOST SHIPPING REGIONS. BY FRIDAY
THE LOW PRESSURE OUT TO THE W OF THE UK MOVS A LITTLE E
INTO PORTPATRICK WHILST SLACK FLOW MAINTAINS ACROSS THE
E. THERE IS A LOW RISK OF A DEEP LOW DEVELOPING ACROSS
NERN PARTS OF CULLERCOATS DURING FRIDAY WITH A RISK OF
GALES BUT CURRENTLY THIS LOOKS UNLIKELY WITH MAINLY
LIGHT WINDS CURRENTLY EXP THROUGH THE PERIOD
